{"name":"Scarlet Brotherhood Sample Events","permission":{"default":0,"0WeUA5DIO5y5btuC":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"ZSio3LUWcIxAVLte","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Brotherhood slips evidence of smuggling to the guard, causing several popular fishing boat owners to be arrested.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BV5QqWpMO7cJgYqV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Brotherhood’s agents spread rumors that the mine is on the verge of failure and the crown plans to award the dwarves rulership of Saltmarsh as compensation.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0gNvcIMCLi0iz8y7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Brotherhood blackmails Ingo the Drover and Keledek the Unspoken, two people in town with dark pasts, into their service, turning them into useful agents.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FUYSh014irw2XptX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Tainted grain delivered by a merchant in league with the Brotherhood leads to an outbreak of plague.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6ZV2jSoJEvsmaGMk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The Brotherhood uses kidnapping, blackmail, or other sinister means to turn an important member of another faction into an ally.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[15,16],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oJo5txfrMXzzcJTj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A small band of escaped slaves arrives in town. They claim that several sailors at the docks once worked as slave traders, prompting outraged calls for justice from Anders.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[17,18],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lWv2aRxCOIcoM7P5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Pirate activity increases, bearing the unmistakable mark of the Sea Princes. The Brotherhood’s ships adopt Sea Prince regalia to confuse the issue.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3AGmFtVg93jn42ZF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Skerrin, growing bored and overconfident, assassinates a prominent member of a faction and tries to frame the Sea Princes for the deed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"2aMqahOkX3FYddpE"}
{"_id":"7cywxu09ubQ50G63","name":"Loyalist Sample Events","permission":{"default":0},"sort":200001,"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"Cmtn8XUPKoQEBHo3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The town guard cracks down on smuggling, going house to house in search of contraband.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8RRzMKPWDBCEeXO6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A tribe of marauders (gnolls, orcs, or goblins) moves into the area, putting the town on alert and forcing Eliander to call out the militia. The traditionalists chafe under his orders.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lVM7jXMbb5d85Ief","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A mass breakout allows a crew of smugglers to escape the dungeons, increasing tension in town.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2Xyw1ccuAV6jIMqS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The dwarves make a spectacular find in the mine, sparking plans to expand their presence and the docks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"B0cwW5XyibdzDB18","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Eliander and the town guard are called away to help deal with a threat from the Dreadwood, leaving behind only a skeleton crew to keep the peace and watch the mine.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[15,16],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6hb2qQYahA43QMrv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A new wave of immigrants from the north arrives in town, tilting the population such that the loyalists might win a majority in the next town council election.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[17,18],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jGieIkesZQOoEdzs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A bloody battle against pirates leaves a Keoish naval squadron undermanned. The squadron comes to town to press local sailors into service. Eliander secretly passes along the names of hotheaded traditionalists for the press gangs to target.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2qqA9XvzreYe089r","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"\tHaving found enough evidence to charge him, Eliander seizes Gellan and ships him to Seaton to face charges of smuggling. Riots break out in town.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false}
{"name":"Saltmarsh Mood","permission":{"default":0,"0WeUA5DIO5y5btuC":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"5YFQtl1Pdu79BIrS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Poor Catch. The townsfolk are frustrated and prone to bickering; everyone is in a bad mood.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VSpsh6p1ueuvdA9B","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Bountiful Catch. Music and merriment echo through town as everyone celebrates.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ie4eyKg4NyQBRK6z","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"\tTypical Catch. Overall, the fishers are content with their recent results. Here and there, crews boast of good pickings or bemoan their poor haul.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"SSTrvCt1k940eFHC"}
{"name":"Manistrad Jobs","permission":{"default":0,"0WeUA5DIO5y5btuC":3},"flags":{},"description":"Those who seek an audience with Manistrad can find her here when she’s not working at the mine. She sometimes has need for adventurers to help keep the mining operation secure. Roll a d6 and consult the table below to determine the nature of an available task.","results":[{"_id":"YWJUABBS1PD9iC1d","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Guard a mining shaft that was recently attacked by duergar from the Underdark.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"B7Kzg8TYbJQQc2T0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Escort supply wagons moving to and from Saltmarsh.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"81wGlfSgpCTj7c3U","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Explore a tunnel discovered in the mines that bears signs of troglodyte infestation.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tEl12moUUXS7ctYX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Find a group of miners who went missing underground and may have been snatched by slavers.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2M9hnRW0pOd5UsCA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Track down a thief who stole a shipment of expensive mining gear in Saltmarsh.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"D3LDP2K27yw6PCeM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Locate the source of zombies and skeletons that have been sighted in the mines recently.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":false,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"UTT5mz18nDklCoLS"}
{"name":"Traditionalist Sample Events","permission":{"default":0,"0WeUA5DIO5y5btuC":3},"flags":{},"description":"Ghosts of Saltmarsh Traditionalist Events","results":[{"_id":"mQsAkBhCMeLIm2Wr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A group of fishers accosts dwarves and other outsiders, demanding they leave town or else.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tOG8ZBoLt6KLGRaX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Gellan Primewater imports a variety of exotic flowers that he uses to decorate the town, while also distributing fresh tropical fruit free of charge to the townsfolk.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pD6CPTasJ9H3WOC6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A fire breaks out in town, and Eda Oweland raises funds to support those who lost their homes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JZ47ejQrGZojB0p7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A fishing boat goes missing with its crew. They were smuggling a haul of black pearls, and Gellan wants his treasure back without risking his cover.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Qu9P0cbuAx8FaVLY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A bountiful catch leads to a day of feasting and reconciliation, giving the factions a chance to make amends.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[15,16],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5VCh0ZhVAbB0iDcF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A bungled smuggling operation lands a few respected people in jail, leading to near riots as fishers gather in a huge mob to effect a breakout.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[17,18],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZRktPgXmp0dgoVqx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A horrible sea creature has been sighted, keeping many crews at the docks until it disappears. Anyone who tracks it down and slays it would be a hero. Gellan pledges a magic weapon to its slayer.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Ofvt3QziAN65aBLI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Several fishing crews have gone missing. The locals demand that Keoland dispatch a squadron of ships to track down the slavers from the Sea Princes who surely kidnapped them.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"YuSWj560nMxa0PNG"}
{"name":"Dock Rumors","permission":{"default":0,"0WeUA5DIO5y5btuC":3},"flags":{},"description":"","results":[{"_id":"8zjrODb8AwOSxcIY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The crown dispatched a caravan with enough gold to commission six new warships. It went missing near the Hool Marshes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"q8xFb4uM3X81G8rt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Drow traders posing as surface elves have been doing business in town.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BoLv7ourWtNRkU83","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Someone’s sabotaging fishing boats. It’s those dwarves — they want to take over!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MBfHgRPmqkglfeHK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The king’s agents have infiltrated town. It’s only a matter of time before they remove the council and replace them with foppish nobles.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BVPts0yoU4ciJ5ii","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"That tiefling who’s looking to buy crocodile skulls can’t be up to anything good.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tDDxMKAzZQw31wlm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A couple of fishing boats have gone missing. If the sea devils aren’t behind it, I’m a merman.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gqk0kLQxGFoyjsdN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A big critter’s been going through everyone’s trash at night. Something from the swamp, I’d reckon — maybe a troll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nb45WBaYunGOX3pM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Sometimes on a moonless night, you can meet the ghost of a drowned sailor trying to get home. Lead one to their home, and you’ll get a wish. Fail, and they’ll strangle you.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eVnXICi7mrb6fzz2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"If you see someone at the docks wearing a red cloak after dark, slip them a copper piece and they’ll connect you with smugglers from beyond this world who can sell you anything you’ve dreamed of.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PzkmxFbe8EzNEPc3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"It’s only a matter of time before the dwarves dig too deep and unleash something horrible.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false}],"formula":"d10","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"z4pk2BgVlcJClEga"}
